## Industry-normalized baselines reduce noisy decline alerts

Usage decline interpreted against segment and seasonal baseline produced cleaner
risk classification than absolute thresholding.

Fact: Baseline-normalized usage comparisons reduced false-positive decline alerts in cyclical industries.
Belief: Usage trend models should include industry and fiscal context by default.
Value: Alert precision is more valuable than high alert volume for GTM operations.
Precedent: Prior quarter recalibration improved decline signal reliability across enterprise segments.
